definition.value: Primarily the sexual desire of a stepmother for her stepson, though the term has been extended to cover difficult relationships between stepparents and stepchildren in general.

A theorized inferiority complex normally attributed to people of short stature. It is characterized by overly-aggressive or domineering social behavior, such as lying about earnings, and carries the implication that such behavior is compensatory for the subject's physical or social shortcomings.
A desire to be punished, often employed by psychoanalyst criminologists to explain crime.

A combination of psychiatric and somatic symptoms that are considered to be a recognizable disease only within a specific society or culture. There are no objective biochemical or structural alterations of body organs or functions, and the disease is not recognized in other cultures.
A pathological behavior pattern that is specific to a particular geographic, ethnic, or cultural group.
The sentiment of desiring the ability to become pregnant or the state of being pregnant.

Art forms such as painting, drawing, printmaking, sculpture, ceramics, photography, video, filmmaking, design, crafts, and architecture. Many artistic disciplines such as performing arts, conceptual art, textile arts also involve aspects of visual arts as well as arts of other types. Also included within the visual arts are the applied arts such as industrial design, graphic design, fashion design, interior design and decorative art.
Any specifically defined piece of work that is undertaken or attempted to meet a single requirement.
Any project with artistic components.
Any project with artistic components that pertains to a particular subculture.
Any project with artistic components that pertains to LGBTQIA+ persons or culture or to the LGBTQIA+ community.
A dictionary about or otherwise related to a particular subculture or subcultures.
Dictionaries pertaining especially to LGBTQ persons and/or culture.
A place or collection containing records, documents, or other materials pertaining specifically to asexual persons, communities, or culture.
A place or collection containing records, documents, or other materials pertaining specifically to intersex persons, communities, or culture.
Dictionaries pertaining especially to gay men and/or gay male culture.
Dictionaries pertaining especially to lesbians and/or lesbian culture.
Dictionaries pertaining especially to bisexuality and/or bisexual culture.
Dictionaries pertaining especially to transgender people and/or transgender culture.
Dictionaries pertaining especially to intersex conditions, intersex people and/or intersex culture.
Dictionaries pertaining especially to asexuality and/or asexual culture.

A reference book containing an alphabetical list of slang, which is vernacular vocabulary not generally acceptable in formal usage, usually including information given for each word, including meaning, pronunciation, and etymology.
An alphabetical list of technical terms in some specialized field of knowledge; usually published as an appendix to a text on that field.
A glossary of terms related to a particular subculture.
A glossary of terms related to LGBTQIA+ persons and/or culture.
A glossary of terms related to lesbian people and/or lesbian culture.
A glossary of terms related to gay men and/or gay male culture.
A glossary of terms related to bisexuality and/or bisexual culture.
A glossary of terms related to transgender people and/or transgender culture.
A glossary of terms related to intersex conditions, intersex people and/or intersex culture.
A glossary of terms related to asexuality and/or asexual culture.
A glossary of terms related to medicine.
Parties specific to the transgender community and transgender people.
A party held in order to "repeal" a transgender person's sex assigned at birth and celebrate their gender identity.
A party whose primary purpose is to give gifts to the guest of honor.

A celebration during which parents, friends and family find out the sex of a baby. This has become possible with the increasing accuracy of various technologies of determining the baby's sex before birth. It is a relatively new phenomenon and distinct from a baby shower, which is a gift-giving ceremony.
A party of gift-giving or a ceremony that has different names in different cultures. It celebrates the delivery or expected birth of a child or the transformation of a woman into a mother.
Affection without any limitations, or love without conditions. This term is sometimes associated with other terms such as true altruism or complete love.
Love touted as unconditional, but potentially dependent on one's status or identity, for example, if one is gay or transgender.
Any small-scale verbal or physical interaction between those of different races, cultures, beliefs, or genders that has no malicious intent, but that can be interpreted as an aggression.

A demographic group (whether based on ethnicity, race or religion) whose members are perceived to achieve a higher degree of socioeconomic success than the population average. This success is typically measured relatively by income, education, low criminality and high family/marital stability.
An explicit racial derogation; verbal/nonverbal; e.g. name-calling, avoidant behavior, purposeful discriminatory actions.
Communications that convey rudeness and insensitivity and demean a person's racial heritage or identity; subtle snubs; unknown to the perpetrator; hidden insulting message to the recipient of color.
Communications that exclude, negate, or nullify the psychological thoughts, feelings, or experiential reality of a person belonging to a particular group.
A man who is not intersex.
A woman who is not intersex.
A child who is intersex.
Boys in a small community in the Dominican Republic whose penises appear to miraculously appear at the onset of puberty at around age twelve, causing them to be mistaken as girls until that point.
A childhood-aged person belonging to any of various minority groups.
An childhood-aged person belonging to any of various ethnic minority groups.
A young person who is gender nonconforming.
